data.description: Views! Views! Views! This prestigious home sits on arguably one of the best lots in all of Erie Highlands. Perched above open space, the views captured from your back porch are utterly breathtaking. Enjoy stunning Rocky Mountain landscapes while enjoying your first cup of coffee in the morning. The covered patio has a ceiling fan and sun shades. The yard has extensive landscaping with a raised vegetable garden and custom fire-pit. There are walking trails all throughout the neighborhood to take advantage of year-round. This home also sits on a cul-de-sac street so there is less traffic.  Not to be outdone by its exterior beauty, the inside of this home does not disappoint. Your main floor living boasts a custom, gourmet kitchen. Ceiling height cabinets, an expansive island, range hood, double ovens, a large walk-in pantry, and Kitchenaid appliances. The cozy family room off to the side offers a bank of west-facing windows and a tiled fireplace to turn on during our crisp winter months. There is a formal dining space for large gatherings, as well as an informal front living room.  The main-floor bedroom shares the views, a well-appointed bathroom, and a laundry room for convenience.  There is a fully finished basement with a large great room, a guest bedroom, and a bathroom. Walk-out access to the backyard to enjoy the firepit...and you guessed it: the views! The upper level of the home has 3 auxiliary bedrooms (all with walk-in closets), an additional full bath, family room, and the Primary Suite. The Primary Suite boasts tray ceilings, built-in shelves, a ceiling fan, mountain views, and an en-suite bathroom. The dual-entry shower is the gem of the space, a stand-alone tub, and heated floors make this bathroom a true treat. Erie Highlands is a master-planned community with parks, playgrounds, trails, a clubhouse, a pool, and a fitness center. Located within minutes of the historic downtown Erie area and located near shopping, coffee stops, and restaurants.
